---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '../../components/Navigation.astro';

const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout>
  <Navigation />
  <div class="container">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>mTLS and Certificates: A Crash Course</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">A comprehensive guide to mutual TLS authentication and X.509 certificates</p>
    </header>

    <section class="intro">
      <p>This crash course provides comprehensive coverage of mutual TLS (mTLS) and X.509 certificates, drawing from authoritative sources including DigiCert, SSL.com, and other reputable Certificate Authorities.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="contents">
      <h2>Contents</h2>
      
      <div class="section-group">
        <h3>Core Concepts</h3>
        <div class="chapters-grid">
          <a href={`${baseUrl}security/introduction`} class="chapter-card">
            <span class="chapter-number">1</span>
            <div class="chapter-content">
              <h4>Introduction to TLS and mTLS</h4>
              <p>Learn the fundamentals of Transport Layer Security and mutual authentication</p>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href={`${baseUrl}security/x509-certificates`} class="chapter-card">
            <span class="chapter-number">2</span>
            <div class="chapter-content">
              <h4>Understanding X.509 Certificates</h4>
              <p>Deep dive into the structure and components of digital certificates</p>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href={`${baseUrl}security/certificate-authorities`} class="chapter-card">
            <span class="chapter-number">3</span>
            <div class="chapter-content">
              <h4>Certificate Authorities and PKI</h4>
              <p>Explore the role of CAs and public key infrastructure</p>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href={`${baseUrl}security/cryptography-fundamentals`} class="chapter-card">
            <span class="chapter-number">4</span>
            <div class="chapter-content">
              <h4>Public Key Cryptography Fundamentals</h4>
              <p>Understand the cryptographic principles behind certificates</p>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-group">
        <h3>Implementation</h3>
        <div class="chapters-grid">
          <a href={`${baseUrl}security/mtls-handshake`} class="chapter-card">
            <span class="chapter-number">5</span>
            <div class="chapter-content">
              <h4>How Mutual TLS Works</h4>
              <p>Step-by-step guide to the mTLS handshake process</p>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href={`${baseUrl}security/public-vs-private-pki`} class="chapter-card">
            <span class="chapter-number">6</span>
            <div class="chapter-content">
              <h4>Public PKI vs Private PKI</h4>
              <p>Compare public and private certificate infrastructure options</p>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href={`${baseUrl}security/use-cases`} class="chapter-card">
            <span class="chapter-number">7</span>
            <div class="chapter-content">
              <h4>mTLS Use Cases and Applications</h4>
              <p>Real-world scenarios where mTLS provides security benefits</p>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-group">
        <h3>Operations</h3>
        <div class="chapters-grid">
          <a href={`${baseUrl}security/best-practices`} class="chapter-card">
            <span class="chapter-number">8</span>
            <div class="chapter-content">
              <h4>Security Best Practices</h4>
              <p>Essential practices for managing certificates and mTLS</p>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href={`${baseUrl}security/troubleshooting`} class="chapter-card">
            <span class="chapter-number">9</span>
            <div class="chapter-content">
              <h4>Common Issues and Troubleshooting</h4>
              <p>Solutions to common mTLS implementation challenges</p>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href={`${baseUrl}security/conclusion`} class="chapter-card">
            <span class="chapter-number">10</span>
            <div class="chapter-content">
              <h4>Conclusion and Next Steps</h4>
              <p>Summary and recommendations for implementation</p>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-group">
        <h3>Reference</h3>
        <div class="chapters-grid">
          <a href={`${baseUrl}security/glossary`} class="chapter-card">
            <span class="chapter-number">ðŸ“š</span>
            <div class="chapter-content">
              <h4>Glossary of Terms</h4>
              <p>Definitions of key terms and concepts</p>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="key-takeaways">
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>mTLS extends standard TLS by authenticating both client and server</li>
        <li>X.509 certificates bind identities to public keys through digital signatures</li>
        <li>Certificate Authorities provide the trust foundation for PKI</li>
        <li>Public PKI is changing with dual-EKU deprecation affecting mTLS implementations</li>
        <li>Private PKI offers control and flexibility for internal use cases</li>
        <li>Proper certificate lifecycle management is critical for security and uptime</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="resources">
      <h2>Additional Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>DigiCert PKI Resources:</strong> <a href="https://www.digicert.com/what-is-pki" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.digicert.com/what-is-pki</a></li>
        <li><strong>SSL.com X.509 Documentation:</strong> <a href="https://www.ssl.com/faqs/what-is-an-x-509-certificate/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.ssl.com/faqs/what-is-an-x-509-certificate/</a></li>
        <li><strong>RFC 5280:</strong> Internet X.509 Public Key Infrastructure Certificate and CRL Profile</li>
        <li><strong>RFC 8446:</strong> The Transport Layer Security (TLS) Protocol Version 1.3</li>
        <li><strong>CA/Browser Forum:</strong> <a href="https://cabforum.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://cabforum.org</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #111827;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #6b7280;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .intro {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto 4rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .intro p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: #4b5563;
  }

  .contents {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .contents h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #111827;
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #e5e7eb;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section-group {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .section-group h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #374151;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .chapters-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .chapter-card {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .chapter-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 12px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    border-color: #3b82f6;
  }

  .chapter-number {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #3b82f6;
    min-width: 2.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    height: 2.5rem;
    background: #eff6ff;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .chapter-content {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .chapter-content h4 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #111827;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .chapter-content p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #6b7280;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .key-takeaways,
  .resources {
    background: #f9fafb;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .key-takeaways h2,
  .resources h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #111827;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .key-takeaways ul,
  .resources ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .key-takeaways li,
  .resources li {
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.6;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
  }

  .key-takeaways li:last-child,
  .resources li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .key-takeaways li::before {
    content: "âœ“ ";
    color: #3b82f6;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
  }

  .resources a {
    color: #3b82f6;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .resources a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
    .container {
      padding: 2rem 1rem;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .subtitle {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .chapters-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>

